The paper deals with geometric data structures and algorithms, specifically for the closest-pair problem in the plane. This suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a likely category. The paper also presents data structures with optimal or near-optimal space and query time, indicating that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are also possible categories. The use of logarithmic query time suggests that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) may also be a relevant category. Finally, the paper settles open questions from a conference on computational geometry, suggesting that cs.GR (Graphics) may also be a possible category.
